AUTHORITIES in the Ministry for Land, Water, Energy and Housing have urged members of the public to plant more trees and establish home gardens because they are important agents of addressing climate change impacts. The deputy minister, Mr Juma Makungu Juma, made the call while answering questions from backbenchers, who wanted to know what the government was doing to promote tree planting, particularly in deforested areas. In his supplementary answers, the Minister for Housing, Ms Salama Aboud Talib, laid emphasis on importance of each household establishing a home garden and planting more trees to beautify the environment, as one of the effective strategies of minimizing the impacts of climate change. The government has been taking different various measures to address the challenge, including increasing public awareness, discouraging tree felling and promoting tree planting.